1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ The Wing Gambit is not very sound, but you do need to know some theory! }
2... cxb4 { Of course, we take the pawn! } 3. a3 e5
{ This is the fourth most played move, but I believe it's the simplest way to punish the gambit. }
4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bc4 Nf6 6. Ng5
{ This is met by a standard reply from the Fried Liver Attack. } 6... d5 7.
exd5 { But now... } 7... b5 { Secures the edge in all variations: } 8. Bxb5
Qxd5 9. c4 bxc3 10. Nxc3 Qxg2 { Why not take the pawn? } 11. Qf3 Qxf3 12. Nxf3
Bd7 { With an extra pawn in the endgame for Black. } *

