1. e4 c5 2. f4 d5
{ Of course, we can play  2...g6  and try to transpose but why not punish White for playing  f4  too early? }
3. exd5 Nf6
{ We would like to take on d5 with the knight and not worried about c4. } 4.
Bb5+ Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Qxd7 6. c4 e6
{ This is a typical idea to get dynamic piece play for the pawn. } 7. Qe2 Bd6
{ Black's goal is rapid development. } 8. d3 O-O 9. dxe6 fxe6 10. Nf3 Nc6 11.
O-O Rae8 { Black is going for the energetic ...e5 push next. } 12. Nc3 e5 13.
f5
{ White has to give up the pawn to try to slow Black down, other moves are not very good. }
13... Nd4 14. Qd1 h6
{ Black stops Bg5 and plans to play  15.--  15...Nxf5  next with a comfortable position. }
