[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. c4
{ White plans to play Nc3, g3, Bg2, Nge2 with a flexible setup known as the Botvinnik English since he can also start with @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.c4  . }
2... g6 3. Nc3 { 3.Nf3  Bg7!  4.d4  Qa5+!  see 2.Nf3 & c4 Anti-Maroczy Setup. }
3... Bg7 4. g3 Nc6 5. Bg2 a6
{ A rare move that many White players underestimate and answer with the autopilot  6.Nge2  . }
6. Nge2 b5
{ The point! Black happily sacrifices the pawn and gets huge Benko-style counterplay. }
7. cxb5 axb5 8. Nxb5 Ba6 9. Nbc3
{ The most common move, but Black is actually better! For example: } 9... Nb4
{ Now you can see the point of the pawn sac. Black takes control over d3-square with some serious threats.   9...h5!?  is strong as well  10.O-O  h4↑  with a big attack. }
10. O-O Bd3
{ Creating total paralysis of the queenside. White's only move to free the position is: }
11. a3 Bc2 12. Qe1 Nd3 { Wins the queen! } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
