{ This is a solid choice. The drawback is that after  9.e5  Black often has to play for equality with minimal winning chances. }
9. Bf4 Nd7 { Black's idea is to play ..e5 and solidify the center } 10. O-O-O
e5 11. Bg5 f6 12. Be3
{ 12.Bh4  g5  13.Bg3  Nc5⩱  Black's a bit better with a flexible structure, while White's bishop on  g3  is stuck. }
12... Bc5
{ Remember that Black is happy to trade the dark square bishops in these symmetrical structures }
13. Bxc5 Nxc5
{ The game is even, here's a possible line:  14.Rd6  Ke7  15.Rhd1  h5  16.b4  Ne6  17.Bxe6  Bxe6=  White's control of the d-file is harmless. I believe that Black's bishop is better than the knight, giving us practical winning chances. }
