[Black "6.Be3 Bg7 7.Nxc6 bxc6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is my recommended way to play this opening as by attacking the e4-pawn we sidestep the Maroczy Bind  4...Nc6  4.c4  . }
5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Be3
{ With this move we transpose into the main Accelerated Dragon setup! } 6...
Bg7 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. e5 Ng8
{ Surprisingly, this retreat is the best move for Black! The knight is heading to f5 via h6. }
9. Bd4 f6
{ I prefer to undermine the center right away, but  9...Qa5  is fine as well. }
10. Qe2 fxe5 11. Bxe5 Nf6 12. O-O-O O-O
{ We've reached a typical double-edged position where I prefer Black due to his central pawns and half-open b-file. The game could continue: }
13. Qe1
{ This was played by GM Delchev in 2021.   13.h4  Qa5  14.h5  Ba6!  15.Qe1  Bxf1  16.Rxf1  gxh5⩱  . }
13... d6 14. Bc4+ Kh8 15. Ne4 { 15.Bxf6  Bxf6∓  . } 15... Qc7 16. Bxf6 Rxf6
{ An incredible exchange sac idea. } 17. Nxf6 Bxf6
{ Black's dark-squared bishop is worth a rook here! Black has full compensation, for example:  18.h4  d5  19.Bb3  a5  20.a4  Rb8  21.h5  gxh5  22.Rxh5  Bg4⩱  . }
*

