1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is my recommended way to play this opening as by attacking the e4-pawn we sidestep the Maroczy Bind  4...Nc6  4.c4  . }
5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Be3
{ With this move we transpose into the main Accelerated Dragon setup! } 6...
Bg7 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. e5 Ng8
{ Surprisingly, this retreat is the best move for Black! The knight is heading to f5 via h6. }
9. f4 Nh6 10. Qd2 d6 { Black immediately undermines White's center. } 11. exd6
Nf5 { An excellent pawn sac for initiative. } 12. O-O-O O-O 13. dxe7
{ It's quite risky to take the pawn.   13.Bf2  is a better try but after  13...Rb8!  with the attack, for example:  14.d7  Bxd7!  Black sacs a piece  15.Qxd7  Qa5  with a huge threat of ...Rxb2! Black has a big attack. }
13... Qxe7 14. Bf2 Be6 15. g4 Rab8
{ Black happily sacs the knight, setting up a devastating blow. } 16. Na4
{ 16.gxf5  Qb4-+  and White is lost. } 16... Rxb2
{ Incredible! White thought he defended b2, didn't he? } 17. Nxb2 Qa3 18. c4
Bc3 19. Qc2 Rb8
{ And White is totally busted as in the game: Vainio, V - Verkasalo, T @@StartBracket@@2073@@EndBracket@@ Helsinki 2000. The game continued:  20.Rd3  Rxb2  21.Qxc3  Rb3+  22.Kd2  Qxa2+  23.Qc2  Rb2-+  winning the queen and the game. }
