[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) Accelerated Dragon − 5...Nc6 6.Be3"]
[Black "6.Be3 Bg7 7.Bc4 Qa5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is my recommended way to play this opening as by attacking the e4-pawn we sidestep the Maroczy Bind  4...Nc6  4.c4  . }
5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Be3
{ With this move we transpose into the main Accelerated Dragon setup! } 6...
Bg7 7. Bc4 { This is the main line. } 7... Qa5
{ I prefer this simple move to force White to castle short. However,  7...O-O  is totally fine and was my recommendation back in 2005 in Chess Openings Explained for Black. }
8. f3 { Allows a beautiful trap. } 8... Qb4 9. Bb3 Nxe4
{ The point! Black opens up the g7–bishop. } 10. Nxc6 { 10.fxe4  Bxd4  -+ }
10... Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 Qxc3+ 12. Ke2 dxc6 13. Bd4
{ It looks as though Black is busted since both the queen, rook, and knight are all under attack but...   Note that  13.fxe4  will be answered by  13...Bg4+  . }
13... e5
{ A beauty!  This solves all of Black's problems and gives us a winning edge after. }
14. Bxc3 Nxc3+ 15. Kf2 Nxd1+ 16. Raxd1 O-O *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2) Accelerated Dragon − 5...Nc6 6.Be3"]
[Black "6.Be3 Bg7 7.Bc4 Qa5 #2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is my recommended way to play this opening as by attacking the e4-pawn we sidestep the Maroczy Bind  4...Nc6  4.c4  . }
5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Be3
{ With this move we transpose into the main Accelerated Dragon setup! } 6...
Bg7 7. Bc4 { This is the main line. } 7... Qa5
{ I prefer this simple move to force White to castle short. However,  7...O-O  is totally fine and was my recommendation back in 2005 in Chess Openings Explained for Black. }
8. O-O O-O
{ White has two plans here:  A@@EndBracket@@  9.Bb3  with idea to use the d5-outpost in the future  B@@EndBracket@@  9.Nb3  to gain a tempo on the queen and retreat the bishop to e2. }
9. Nb3 Qc7 10. f4 d6 11. Be2
{ This is now a Classical Dragon with ...Qc7 inserted. Black is doing fine. }
11... a6 12. a4 Be6 13. Bf3 Na5 { With nice counterplay! } *

