{ With this move we've transposed to a normal Dragon. The only difference is having the queen on a5, which is not that bad. Due to the ...Ng4 threat White typically reacts with  10.h3  or  10.f3  . }
10. h3 Bd7 11. Re1
{ White strengthens the center and gets ready to play Nd5 at the right moment. }
11... Rac8 12. Nf3
{ White avoids trades and aims to take advantage of his extra space. } 12...
Be6
{ I like this rare idea that was never played at GM level. Black doesn't mind the doubled pawns as he will control the key d5 outpost }
13. Ng5 Bxb3 14. axb3 Qd8 15. Qe2 a6
{ With rough equality as was played in a correspondence game: Mikhalchuk, V-Uryupin, I ICCF email 2011. }
