[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This is my recommended way to play this opening as by attacking the e4-pawn we sidestep the Maroczy Bind  4...Nc6  4.c4  . }
5. Nc3 d6
{ In this chapter, I will cover all the other setups for White, except for the 6.Be3, f3, Qd2 setup known as the Yugoslav Attack. }
6. h3
{ Similarly to  6.f3  White wants to establish control of g4 for further Be3, Qd2 setup. }
6... Bg7 7. Be3 O-O 8. Qd2 d5
{ This is much stronger here as White's pawn is not on f3, thus allowing us to meet e5 with ...Ne4! }
9. e5 Ne4 10. Nxe4 dxe4 11. Bf4 Qb6 { Followed by ...Rd8 with counterplay. } *

