5. Bb5+ Nd7
{ I like this simple approach more than the common ...Nc6, so we don't have to worry about Bxc6+, ruining our structure. }
6. d4 e6 7. O-O a6
{ I like the idea of challenging the bishop early to give White a choice. } 8.
Bd3 Bxf3
{ I recommend taking as soon as possible before White gets to play Nbd2 and recaptures with the knight. }
9. Qxf3 Qb6 { Black puts immediate pressure on d4. } 10. Rd1 Ne7 11. Na3 Bg7
12. Nc2 O-O
{ Black has a solid setup with a typical French idea to undermine the e5-pawn with ...f6. For example: }
13. Rb1 cxd4 14. cxd4 f6 15. exf6 Nxf6 16. Qe2 Nf5
{ With active piece play for Black. } *

