{ White has several options here, all leading to easy play for Black. } 7. Nc3
{ This leads to a ruined structure after: } 7... Bxf3 8. Qxf3
{ leads to a bad endgame for White } 8... Nxd4 9. Qxd5 Qxd5 10. Nxd5 Rd8
{ a key intermezzo! } 11. Ne3 Bg7
{ Black is much better here, for example:  12.f4  f6!  13.exf6  Nxf6  14.Bc4  b5!  15.Bb3  Ne4  with total domination, natural  16.O-O?  loses after  16...Nxb3  17.axb3  Nc5!  18.Rxa7  Bd4-+  . }
