5. Bd2 Qb6
{ The pressure on d4 & b2 forces White to put his bishop on c3, where it's clearly misplaced. }
6. Bc3 cxd4 7. Nxd4 { This leads to a harmless bind after: } 7... Nf6 8. Nd2 d6
9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O Nfd7 { Putting pressure on the d4-knight. } 11. N2f3 Nc5 12.
Qc2 e5 { An unusual idea for the bind, but it works great here! } 13. Nb3 Nc6
14. Rad1 Qc7 15. h3 a5
{ Black has a nice flexible structure while White's pieces lack any harmony. }
