1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. Bc4
{ White goes for natural development first, keeping the option to play d3 or c3 & d4 next. }
3... Bg7 4. c3
{ White's most ambitious option. They want to take over the center with d4 next. }
4... e6
{ It's important to have the option to fight in the center with a timely ...d5! }
5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Nf6
{ This rare move has only been played in one correspondence game in 2020. } 7.
e5 Ne4 8. Nf3 { 8.Qe2  d5! } 8... d5 { Black strikes the center with a tempo! }
9. exd6
{ 9.Bb5+  Bd7  10.Bxd7+  Nxd7⩱  leads to a good French structure for Black. }
9... Nxd6 10. Bb3 O-O 11. O-O Nc6
{ The game is roughly even, but I prefer Black due to the central e-pawn.  Becker,C @@StartBracket@@2204@@EndBracket@@-Masset,J  @@StartBracket@@2022@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2020. }
