1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. h4
{ This is a popular move, especially in blitz. White wants to blow open the h-file with h5 with an easy attack. }
3... h5
{ I like this simple approach to stop h5 once and for all. White now needs to find a new plan, which is not easy. }
4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6
{ We happily transpose to the regular Accelerated Dragon where the inclusion of h4 & ...h5 favors Black. }
6. Nc3 Nc6 7. Be2 Bg7 8. Be3 O-O 9. Qd2 d5
{ Black's famous idea in the Accelerated Dragon works great here. } *

