{ This just is easily parried, we have nothing to worry about. } 5... e6 6. Nc3
{ 6.Qf3?!  Nh6⩱  followed by ...Nc6 & Ne5 ideas. } 6... Nc6 7. d3 Nge7 8. Be3
{ Walks into a famous trap } 8... d5 9. exd5 exd5 10. Bb3 f6
{ The immediate  10...d4  is a mistake due to  11.Bxf7+  Kf8  12.O-O  dxc3  13.Qf3  and in this position White attacking changes compensate for the lost piece. }
11. Nf3 d4 { Wins a piece without any compensation for White. } *

