Ng5 { This is not dangerous at all. } 7... e6
{ Now White's c4 bishop is biting on granite! } 8. a3
{ White's typical idea in these structures. They prepare the retreat on a2. }
8... Nf6 { I prefer this over 8...Nge7 but either option is fine. } 9. Ba2 O-O
10. Bf4 Rb8
{ Black goes for the simple plan of ...b5, which is easy to remember: the Dragon swings with his tail! }
11. O-O b5 12. Ne2 a5 13. c3 a4
{ I prefer Black due to the flexible structure and easy play, while it's not clear how White can generate any attack. }
