10. Be2 Nc6 11. Nxc6 bxc6
{ Black's pawn structure on the queenside is slightly weakened but the control over d5 matters more! }
12. O-O Nf5 13. Bf3 O-O { Black enters a forcing line after } 14. Bxc6 Nxe3 15.
fxe3 Qxe3+ 16. Kh1 Rb8
{ He's clearly better due to the bishop pair and pressure on b2 } *

