{ This is the point! } 18. Bxe5 { 18.Bg3?  Nh5∓  . } 18... Rxe5 19. Rxe5 Qxe5
20. Nxe5 Bxf3 21. Ndxf3 Rxb2
{ The dust has settled, and Black is doing fine in this endgame. Yes, White has a strong c-pawn, but Black's rook is a monster on the 2nd rank. White can easily get in trouble here. For example  22.c5  Nd5  23.Rc1  Rxa2  24.c6  24...Ra5!   @@StartBracket@@  24...Nc7  25.Rd1⇆  @@EndBracket@@  What an amazing idea! White can't push the pawn while Black just wants to play ...Nc7  25.h3   @@StartBracket@@  25.c7?  Nxc7  26.Rxc7  Ra1+-+  Oops.@@EndBracket@@  25...Nc7  26.Nd3  Ra1!  27.Rxa1  Bxa1-+  .  Believe it or not, but this endgame is now winning for Black due to the outside a-pawn passers. Stockfish gives -4 here! }
*

