[Black "Smith-Morra Gambit #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3
{ In the past I have recommended a simple move  3...g6  to sidestep the Smith-Morra. While it's a good surprise weapon, in this course I have decided to focus on the refutation instead. }
4. Nxc3 Nc6 5. Nf3 e6 6. Bf4
{ The second most popular move, White wants to play Nb5 } 6... Bb4
{ This simple developing move is my antidote against most tries by White. } 7.
Bc4 Nge7 8. O-O Bxc3
{ A thematic idea. Black takes the knight right away after White castles. } 9.
bxc3 d5 10. exd5 exd5 11. Bd3 O-O
{ Black's king is safe here. It's important to note that a Greek Gift sacrifice doesn't work here. }
12. Bxh7+
{ 12.Ng5  is easily parried with  12...Bf5  13.Bxf5  Nxf5  14.Qh5  h6  15.Nf3  Qf6∓  . }
12... Kxh7 13. Ng5+ Kg8 14. Qh5 Bf5 { and White is just lost } *

