{ This is a thematic idea in this line. } 8. c3 N4c6
{ So far, we are following Morozevich, A-Andreikin, A 2018. } 9. Qe3
{ A clever move, trying to tie Black down.   9.exd7+  Nxd7  allows Black easy development. }
9... dxe6 10. Qxc5 Bh6
{ An improvement over the game, taking away e3 square from the queen.   10...e5  11.Qe3∞  was the game: Morozevich, A @@StartBracket@@2665@@EndBracket@@-Andreikin, D @@StartBracket@@2712@@EndBracket@@ Moscow 2018. }
11. O-O-O Nd7 12. Qc4 Nb6 13. Qh4 Bg5
{ Pushing around White's queen all over the board. } 14. Qg3 e5 15. Bd3 Be6
{ Followed by ...Qd7 and ...O-O-O Black has an easy game. But I want to show you a cool idea vs. the natural  16.Nh3  . }
16. Nh3 Bh4 { Black takes over the initiative with this cool tactic. } 17. Qxh4
Qxd3 *

