[White "20) Wing Gambit 2.b4"]
[Black "2.b4 cxb4 3.a3 e5 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ The Wing Gambit is not very sound, but you do need to know some theory! }
2... cxb4 { Of course, we take the pawn! } 3. a3 e5
{ This is the fourth most played move, but I believe it's the simplest way to punish the gambit. }
4. axb4 Bxb4 5. c3 Be7
{ Black finds the best square for the bishop as on c5 it's going to get hit with d4 }
6. d4 Nf6 { A rare-move but it's the best } 7. Bd3 d5
{ Black blows open the center. } 8. dxe5 Nxe4 9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O Nc6 11. Bf4
Bg4
{ Black finishes the development first @@StartBracket@@!@@EndBracket@@ and still has the extra pawn. }
