[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. b4
{ The Wing Gambit is not very sound, but you do need to know some theory! }
2... cxb4 { Of course, we take the pawn! } 3. a3 e5
{ This is the fourth most played move, but I believe it's the simplest way to punish the gambit. }
4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb2 Qb6
{ A rare move with only nine games in the database. Black sets up a cool trap! }
6. Nxe5 bxa3 7. Bc3 a2
{ This is the start of a nice geometric sequence that wins a piece. } 8. Rxa2
Nxe5 9. Bxe5 Qe6 { And White is losing material. He can hang on a bit longer: }
10. Ra5 b6 11. Rd5 f6 { Now the e4-pawn is under fire! } 12. Bb2 Qxe4+ 13. Qe2
Qxe2+ 14. Bxe2
{ White managed to save the piece but has now lost way too many pawns, the game is decided. }
14... Bb7 15. Rd3 Bxg2 16. Rg1 Bc6
{ Black is two pawns up with a winning endgame } *

