[White "22) 2.Be2"]
[Black "2.Be2 g6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 c5 2. Be2
{ This is the recommendation of GingerGM @@StartBracket@@Simon Williams@@EndBracket@@ in this Chessable course: The British Grand Prix. }
2... g6 { We just go for our usual HAD move order here. } 3. f4 Bg7 4. Nf3 Nc6
5. O-O d6 6. c3
{ A bit more cunning move. White is keeping us guessing whether he would play d3 or d4. }
6... Nf6 7. d3
{ 7.e5  is a bit premature due to  7...Nd5  8.d4  cxd4  9.cxd4  O-O⩱  And White's center is a bit too loose. }
7... c4
{ Black has many good moves, but I feel like this is the simplest. White's center gets destroyed, making his attack less likely to succeed. }
8. Kh1 O-O 9. Nbd2 cxd3 10. Bxd3 b6
{ I like this simple approach with the idea to play ...Bb7 next. } 11. Nb3 Bb7
12. Qe2 e5 { A strong novelty with the idea to fight for the center. } 13. fxe5
Nxe5 14. Nxe5 dxe5 15. Bg5 { White's pin is easily broken. } 15... h6 16. Bh4
g5 17. Bg3 Nh5 { Tactics! The Queen is overloaded. } 18. Rad1
{ 19.Qxh5  Qxd3! } 18... Nf4 19. Bxf4 exf4
{ The position is about equal but I prefer Black due to the bishop pair and pressure against the e4-pawn. }
*

