1. e4 c5 2. Be2
{ This is the recommendation of GingerGM @@StartBracket@@Simon Williams@@EndBracket@@ in this Chessable course: The British Grand Prix. }
2... g6 { We just go for our usual HAD move order here. } 3. f4 Bg7 4. Nf3 Nc6
5. O-O d6 6. d3 b5
{ I like this rare space-grabbing move. If White plays so slowly with 2.Be2 and not fighting for the center than we can grab space on the queenside! }
7. c3 Nf6 8. a3 { White stops ...b4 and awaits for us to castle kingside } 8...
O-O 9. Qe1 { Getting ready for the attack } 9... e6
{ with this simple move Black is now ready for Qh4 } 10. f5 exf5 11. Qh4 c4
{ White's center is collapsing and there's no attack. For example: } 12. Bh6
{ In the case of  12.Bg5  cxd3  13.Bxd3  Qb6+!  a nice intermezzo to get out of the pin. And now after  14.Kh1  Nxe4  15.Bxe4  fxe4  -+ Black has too many extra pawns! }
12... cxd3 13. Bxd3 Ne5 { With a big edge for Black. } *

