7. c3 Nf6 8. Qe1 { This is the standard attack for many Grand Prix setups }
8... b4 { Notice that Black hasn't castled yet! } 9. Qh4 Rb8 10. f5
{ White is ready to checkmate as but the problem is...the king is not on g8! }
10... gxf5
{ The point! Black's king is quite happy on e8 and we take over the kingside! }
11. Kh1
{ a useful waiting move, but Black is fine as long as he doesn't castle. }
11... e5 { with idea to play ...f4 next } 12. Bg5 h6
{ and White finds himself in bad position after } 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Qxf6 Bxf6
{ Black's bishop pair and extra pawn give us a big edge. } *

