1. e4 c5 2. Na3
{ This unusual move was popularized by the Russian GM Vadim Zvjagintsev. These days both Carlsen and Rapport play it from time to time. The point is to delay c3 and wait for Black to show their plan. }
2... g6 3. h4 { Carlsen's choice in a blitz game. } 3... h5
{ This is my recommendation vs 2. Nf3 and 3.h4, and it's good here as well. }
4. c3 Bg7 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 d5
{ This is a thematic idea that I also recommend in the Advance Variation. } 7.
exd5 Nf6 8. Bb5+ Nbd7 9. Nf3 O-O 10. O-O Nb6
{ Black will recapture the d5-pawn and will have a pleasant edge vs the IQP structure. }
*

