1. e4 c5 2. Na3
{ This unusual move was popularized by the Russian GM Vadim Zvjagintsev. These days both Carlsen and Rapport play it from time to time. The point is to delay c3 and wait for Black to show their plan. }
2... g6 3. c3 Bg7 4. Nf3
{ 4.d4  cxd4  5.cxd4  d5!  Black undermines the center with this thematic idea  6.exd5   @@StartBracket@@  6.e5  a6  with a simple idea to stop Bb5  7.Nf3  Bg4  8.Be2  transposing to the main line 4.Nf3@@EndBracket@@  6...Nf6  and eventually the d5 pawn will be lost. }
4... a6 { I like this unusual move for a specific reason, after: } 5. d4 cxd4
6. cxd4 d5 { Black achieves the key idea by undermining White's center. } 7. e5
{ 7.exd5  Nf6  is a nice edge for Black vs the IQP. } 7... Bg4
