24. Nc6 Bxc6 25. dxc6 Ra7 26. Re3
{ The losing move by Leela   26.Bd5  keeps the game going, but after  26...Qb6  27.b4!  Rb8  28.Kc1  Qxb4  29.Qxb4  Rxb4  30.Bf3∓  Stockfish claims that White is worse but defendable. }
26... Qa8 { The simple winning move. White can't stop the invasion on a1 } 27.
Kc1 Qxc6 28. Bd5
{ This loses on the spot, but other tries are bad too.   28.Kd2  Qg2+  29.Ke1   @@StartBracket@@  29.Re2  Ne4+-+  @@EndBracket@@  29...Ne4-+   28.Qc4  e6!  with a winning attack }
28... Ra1+ 29. Kd2 Qxd5+ *

