[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Strategy & Tactics"]
[Black "Punish The Bad Bind "]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/pp1pppbp/2n2np1/8/2PNP3/2N2P2/PP4PP/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 0 7"]
[SetUp "1"]

7... Nxe4
{ A simple discovery tactical motif from many Accelerated Dragon positions. After a forced sequence: }
8. Nxc6 Nxc3 9. Nxd8 Nxd1 10. Nxf7 Kxf7 11. Kxd1 Rd8
{ Black is about to play ...d5 and stands clearly better due to an exposed king on d1. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Strategy & Tactics"]
[Black "Kingside Expansion"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "4kbnr/pp3p2/1qr1p1pp/3pP3/3P3B/1P3N2/1P2QPPP/R4RK1 b k - 0 15"]
[SetUp "1"]

15... g5 { An important idea. } 16. Bg3 Ne7
{ Black is about to play ...Nf5, paralyzing White's bishop and knight. } 17. h3
Nf5 18. Rfd1 Rg8
{ Notice that Black's king is completely safe on e8. We have a simple plan of pushing our pawns with a free kingside attack. }
*

