1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6
{ This is the Hyper-Accelerated Dragon move order. Black's idea is to fianchetto the bishop on g7 first, controlling the long diagonal.   Please note that we avoid  2...Nc6  as it allows  3.Bb5  which is known as the Rossolimo Variation, which leads to totally different types of positions. }
3. c3 d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. d4 Bg7 6. Na3 cxd4 7. Bc4 Qe4+ 8. Be3 Nh6
{ 8...dxe3??  9.Bxf7+  Kxf7  10.Ng5++-  . } 9. cxd4 O-O 10. O-O Nf5 11. Re1
Nxe3 12. Rxe3
{ 12.fxe3  Nc6⩱  Black is somewhat better due to the bishop pair. } 12... Qf4
13. g3 Qd6 14. Nb5 Qd8 15. Ne5 e6 16. d5 Bxe5 17. Rxe5 Nd7 18. Re1 Nb6 19. dxe6
Bxe6 20. Bxe6 fxe6 21. Rxe6 Qxd1+ 22. Rxd1 Rac8 23. Rd2 Nc4 24. Rd7 Nb6 25. Rd2
Nc4 26. Rde2 a6 27. Nd6 Nxd6 28. Rxd6 Rfd8 29. Rxd8+ Rxd8 30. Re6 Kf7 31. Rb6
